text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia wanyu is a shrub or tree belonging to the genus Acacia and the subgenus Juliflorae. It is native to an area in the Mid West and Pilbara regions of Western Australia.The bushy tree or shrub typically grows to a height of 1.5 to 5 metres (5 to 16 ft). It blooms from March to July producing yellow flowers.
